Hey <@U07198R7G0Y> - is there a reason why you don't use the default subscription form that comes with every created blog?

Also - if you want to have custom code, I'd recommend you to create a custom module with your layout/script... and use the module in your template instead of throwing everything in a rich-text.

Pro tip:
if you want to modify css/script through your module/hubl you can put something like
```{% require_css %}
&lt;style&gt;
{% scope_css %}
.some-div{}
{% end_scope_css %}
&lt;/style&gt;
{% end_require_css %}```
and

```{% require_js %}
&lt;script&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
{% end_require_js %}```
into the module.html file/area and drop the module variables there. the module.css and module.js are seperated files and won't work with Hubl
